&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;C3 AI (NYSE: AI), is the Enterprise AI application software company. C3 AI delivers a family of fully integrated products including the C3 Agentic AI Platform, an end-to-end platform for developing, deploying, and operating enterprise AI applications, C3 AI applications, a portfolio of industry-specific SaaS enterprise AI applications that enable the digital transformation of organizations globally, and C3 Generative AI, a suite of domain-specific generative AI offerings for the enterprise.&amp;nbsp;Learn more at: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://c3.ai/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;C3 AI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;C3 AI is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Chief of Staff &lt;/strong&gt;to serve as a force multiplier to the Chief Executive Officer. This role is a unique blend of strategy, operations, and execution, partnering directly with the CEO on the most consequential decisions facing the company. The Chief of Staff will drive cross-functional initiatives, operationalize the CEO’s priorities across the executive leadership team, and ensure decisions translate into measurable outcomes across the organization. The role is located onsite at our Redwood City, CA headquarters.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CEO Thought Partnership: &lt;/strong&gt;Serve as a trusted advisor and sounding board to the CEO on strategy, prioritization, and the most important open questions facing the business. Pressure-test thinking with rigor, structure, and intellectual honesty.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Initiatives: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead high-priority, cross-functional initiatives end-to-end — from problem definition and analysis through alignment and execution. Initiatives may span pricing strategy, market entry, organizational design, M&amp;amp;A diligence, or new product bets.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive Operating Cadence: &lt;/strong&gt;Own the rhythms that drive alignment across the company, including executive leadership team meetings, OKR cycles, all-hands, and quarterly planning. Ensure decisions are documented, communicated, and followed through.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Decision Memos and Analysis: &lt;/strong&gt;Translate complex, open-ended business problems into structured plans, decision memos, and data-driven recommendations the CEO and leadership team can act on within compressed timelines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Depth: &lt;/strong&gt;Engage substantively with the product, platform, and data. Read code and architecture documents, query the data warehouse, and reason about technical tradeoffs alongside engineering leadership.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;External Representation: &lt;/strong&gt;Represent the CEO in select internal and external forums, including customer executive briefings, partner discussions, and executive recruiting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Organizational Health: &lt;/strong&gt;Identify gaps, bottlenecks, and broken processes before they surfac

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;C3 AI (NYSE: AI), is the Enterprise AI application software company. C3 AI delivers a family of fully integrated products including the C3 Agentic AI Platform, an end-to-end platform for developing, deploying, and operating enterprise AI applications, C3 AI applications, a portfolio of industry-specific SaaS enterprise AI applications that enable the digital transformation of organizations globally, and C3 Generative AI, a suite of domain-specific generative AI offerings for the enterprise.&amp;nbsp;Learn more at: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://c3.ai/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;C3 AI&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a member of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;C3 AI Data Science&amp;nbsp;team&lt;/strong&gt;,&amp;nbsp;you will work with some of the largest companies on the planet helping them build the next generation of AI-powered enterprise applications on the C3 AI Platform (&lt;a href=&quot;https://c3.ai/customers/&quot;&gt;c3.ai/customers/&lt;/a&gt;). You will work directly with data scientists, software engineers, and subject matter experts in the definition of new analytics capabilities able to provide our customers with the information they need to make proper decisions and enable their digital transformation. You will help find the appropriate machine learning algorithms to answer those questions and implement those on the C3 AI Platform so they can run at scale.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Qualified candidates will have an in-depth knowledge of most common machine learning techniques and their application. You will also understand the limitations of these algorithms and how to tweak them or derive from them to achieve similar results at large-scale.&lt;/p&gt;
